# ============================================================
# DETAIL CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: detail
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines core policy rules for detail records.

scope:
Covers disclosure, retention, revision,
historical access, masking, and export boundaries.

design_intent:
The policy layer must define normative constraints
that remain stable even when runtime or implementation changes.
Detail policy exists to prevent accidental leakage,
unsafe revision, and historical corruption.

policy_classes:
disclosure_class:
- public
- internal
- restricted
- sealed

retention_class:
- ephemeral
- operational
- historical
- audit_mandatory

revision_authority_class:
- local_reviewer
- domain_owner
- high_trust_owner
- audit_only

policy_rules:
- Public detail may be exported only in public-safe form.
- Internal detail may be disclosed only to authorized internal consumers.
- Restricted detail must be masked or blocked outside authority.
- Sealed detail must require explicit high-trust approval.
- Historical detail must remain labeled and separated from current-active detail.
- Audit-mandatory detail must not be silently deleted.
- Canonical detail overwrite without authorized path is prohibited.

allowed_denied_matrix:
- public -> public export allowed
- public -> internal delivery allowed
- internal -> public export denied unless projected summary exists
- restricted -> public export denied
- sealed -> all non-authorized export denied
- historical -> current-active substitution denied
- audit_mandatory -> silent deletion denied

validation_rules:
- disclosure_class is required.
- retention_class is required.
- revision authority must match requested change scope.
- sealed detail must not be down-scoped without high-trust approval.
- historical records must preserve historical labeling.

failure_codes:
- DETAIL_POLICY_DISCLOSURE_CLASS_MISSING
- DETAIL_POLICY_RETENTION_CLASS_MISSING
- DETAIL_POLICY_REVISION_AUTHORITY_DENIED
- DETAIL_POLICY_SEALED_DOWNSCOPE_DENIED
- DETAIL_POLICY_HISTORICAL_LABEL_REQUIRED

example_scenarios:
- A public entity summary may be exported publicly.
- A restricted trust detail must be blocked from public delivery.
- An audit-mandatory historical record must be retained even after active use ends.
